<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="initial-scale=1, width=device-width">
    <title>Traffic Cop Demo</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/normalize.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/demo.css">

    {% block experiment_js %}{% endblock %}
</head>
<body>

<header class="content">
    <h1><a href="/">Traffic Cop Demo</a></h1>
</header>

<nav class="content">
    <ul>
        <li><a href="/page/1" class="little-text">Page 1<span>redirect</span></a></li>
        <li><a href="/page/2" class="little-text">Page 2<span>callback</span></a></li>
        <li><a href="/page/3" class="little-text">Page 3<span>redirect + callback</span></a></li>
    </ul>
</nav>

<div class="content">
{% block page_header %}
    <h2>Using this demo</h2>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <h3>All pages</h3>

    <p>
        You will be either chosen for an experiment or placed in the
        "no variation" group. Repeated visits to that same page will result in
        the same variation (or lack thereof) being shown.
    </p>

    <p>
        Debug information will be shown at the bottom of the page. To clear the
        variation, click the button in the debug area. This will remove the
        cookie for that page and take you back to the home page.
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong>
            Note that you may be selected for the same variation after clearing
            the cookie. Give each page multiple visits and clears to see all
            available variations.
        </strong>
    </p>

    <h3>Page 1</h3>

    <p>
        Upon being chosen for a variation, you will be redirected to the same
        URL, with the variation appended to the query string.
    </p>

    <h3>Page 2</h3>

    <p>
        Upon being chosen for a variation, a custom callback function will be
        executed in place of a redirect.
    </p>

    <h3>Page 3</h3>

    <p>
        A combination of page 1 & page 2. A redirect variation <em>may</em> take
        place, followed by a custom callback function.
    </p>
{% endblock %}
</div>

{% block page_js %}{% endblock %}
</body>
</html>
